\par }\pard\plain \qj\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Priest:}{\fs32  }{\cs47\b\fs36 For unto Thee is due all glory, honor, and worship: to the Father, and to the Son, and to the Holy Spirit: now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. 

\par }\pard \li720\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {People: Amen. {\*\bkmkstart h2}{\*\bkmkend h2}\sect }\sectd \linex0\sectdefaultcl \pard\plain \s19\sb100\sa100\keepn\nowidctlpar\outlinelevel2\adjustright \b\fs36 {\fs40 The First Antiphon
\par }\pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 And the First Antiphon is sung by the chanters. And the priest says the prayer of the
 Antiphon, (but some say it before the exclamation). But the deacon, bowing leaves his place and goes to stand before the icon of Christ, holding his orarion with three fingers of his right hand.
\par }\pard\plain \s19\sb100\sa100\keepn\nowidctlpar\outlinelevel2\adjustright \b\fs36 {\fs40 \sect }\sectd \linex0\sectdefaultcl \pard\plain \s19\sb100\sa100\keepn\nowidctlpar\outlinelevel2\adjustright \b\fs36 {\fs40 The Little Litany
\par }\pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 At the conclusion of the antiphon, the deacon, standing in the usual place, and bowing, saith:
\par }\pard\plain \qj\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Deacon:}{\fs32  }{\cs47\b\fs36 Again and again in peace let us pray to the Lord.}{\fs32  }{People: Lord, have mercy. }{\fs32 
\par }{\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Deacon:}{\fs32  }{\cs47\b\fs36 Help us, save us, have mercy on us, and keep us, O God, by Thy grace. \tab \tab \tab \tab }{People: Lord, have mercy. }{\fs32 
\par }{\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Deacon:}{\fs32  }{\cs47\b\fs36 
Calling to remembrance our most holy, most pure, most blessed, glorious Lady Theotokos and Ever-Virgin Mary, with all the Saints, let us commit ourselves and one another, and all our life unto Christ our God.}{\fs32   }{People: To Thee, O Lord. 
\par }\pard \qc\li360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 The Prayer of the Second Antiphon}{\cs44\i\f1\cf6 
\par }\pard\plain \s45\qj\li576\ri576\sb100\sa100\sl360\slmult1\nowidctlpar\adjustright \f1\fs36\cf15 {\b\i Priest:}{
 O Lord our God, save Thy people and bless Thine inheritance, preserve the fullness of thy Church, sanctify them that love the beauty of Thy house; do Thou glorify Them by Thy divine power, and forsake not us that hope in Thee.
\par }\pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 Exclamation:
\par }\pard\plain \qj\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Priest:}{\fs32  }{\cs47\b\fs36 
For Thine is the dominion, and Thine is the kingdom, and the power and the glory of the Father, and of the Son, and of the Holy Spirit: now and ever, and unto ages of ages. 
\par }\pard \li720\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {People: Amen. {\*\bkmkstart h5}{\*\bkmkend h5}
\par }\pard\plain \s19\sb100\sa100\keepn\nowidctlpar\outlinelevel2\adjustright \b\fs36 {\fs40 \sect }\sectd \linex0\sectdefaultcl \pard\plain \s19\sb100\sa100\keepn\nowidctlpar\outlinelevel2\adjustright \b\fs36 {\fs40 The Second Antiphon
\par }\pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 And the Second antiphon is sung by the chanters; and the deacon doeth in like manner as during the first prayer.
\par }\pard\plain \s19\sb100\sa100\keepn\nowidctlpar\outlinelevel2\adjustright \b\fs36 {\fs40 \sect }\sectd \linex0\sectdefaultcl \pard\plain \s19\sb100\sa100\keepn\nowidctlpar\outlinelevel2\adjustright \b\fs36 {\fs40 The Little Litany
\par }\pard\plain \qj\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Deacon:}{\fs32  }{\cs47\b\fs36 Again and again in peace let us pray to the Lord. 
\par }\pard \li720\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {People: Lord, have mercy. }{\fs32 
\par }\pard \qj\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Deacon:}{\fs32  }{\cs47\b\fs36 Help us, save us, have mercy on us, and keep us, O God, by Thy grace.  \tab \tab \tab \tab \tab 
\par }\pard \li720\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {People: Lord, have mercy. }{\fs32 
\par }\pard \qj\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Deacon:}{\fs32  }{\cs47\b\fs36 
Calling to remembrance our most holy, most pure, most blessed, glorious Lady Theotokos and Ever-Virgin Mary, with all the Saints, let us commit ourselves and one another, and all our life unto Christ our God. 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 
After this, the Deacon entereth through the South door, and goeth to the high place and maketh three metanias, then turneth to face the priest, and boweth, then goeth to his place beside the priest.}{\fs32 
\par }\pard\plain \li720\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {People: To Thee, O Lord. 
\par }\pard \qc\li360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 The Prayer of the Third Antiphon}{\fs32\cf6 
\par }\pard\plain \s45\qj\li576\ri576\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright \f1\fs36\cf15 {\b\i Priest:}{
 O Thou who hast bestowed upon us these common and concordant prayers, and Who hast promised that when two or three are agreed in Thy name, Thou wouldst grant their requests: Do Thou Thyself now fulfill the requests of Thy servants to their pr
ofit, granting us in this present age the knowledge of Thy truth, and in that to come, life everlasting.
\par }\pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 Exclamation:}{\cs44\i\f1\fs4\cf6 
\par }\pard\plain \qj\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Priest:}{\fs32  }{\cs47\b\fs36 For a good God art Thou and the lover of mankind, and to Thee do we send up glory: to the Father, and to the Son, and the Holy Spi
rit: now and ever, and unto the ages of ages.}{\fs32  
\par }\pard \li720\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {People: Amen. {\*\bkmkstart h8}{\*\bkmkend h8}
\par }\pard\plain \s19\sb100\sa100\keepn\nowidctlpar\outlinelevel2\adjustright \b\fs36 {\fs40 \sect }\sectd \linex0\sectdefaultcl \pard\plain \s19\sb100\sa100\keepn\nowidctlpar\outlinelevel2\adjustright \b\fs36 {\fs40 The Small Entrance
\par }\pard\plain \s25\qj\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 
Here the doors are opened for the Small Entry. Then the Third Antiphon is chanted by the singers; or the beatitudes, if it be Sunday. When they come to the Glory, the priest 
and the deacon, standing before the Holy Table, make three reverences. The priest, taking the Holy Gospel, giveth it to the deacon, and they go by way of the right side, behind the Holy Table. And thus coming out by the North side, with candles going befo
re them, they make the Small Entry; and standing in the usual place, both of them bow their heads, and the deacon having said: 'Let us pray to the Lord', the priest saith the Prayer of Entry secretly. 
\par }\pard\plain \qc\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 {\*\bkmkstart h9}{\*\bkmkend h9}Prayer of the Entry}{\cs44\i\f1\cf6 
\par }\pard\plain \s45\qj\li576\ri576\sb100\sa100\sl360\slmult1\nowidctlpar\adjustright \f1\fs36\cf15 {\b\i Priest:}{ O Master, Lord our God, who
 hast appointed in the heavens ranks and hosts of angels and archangels unto the service of Thy glory: With our entry do Thou cause the entry of the holy angels, serving and glorifying Thy goodness with us. For unto Thee is due all glory, honor, and worsh
ip: to the Father, and to the Son, and to the Holy Spirit, now and ever and unto the ages of ages. Amen. 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\qj\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 When the prayer is ended, the deacon says to the priest, pointing toward the east with his right hand, holding therein his orarion with three fingers:
\par }\pard\plain \s45\qj\li576\ri576\sb100\sa100\sl360\slmult1\nowidctlpar\adjustright \f1\fs36\cf15 {\b\i Deacon:}{ Bless, master, the holy entrance.
\par }\pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 And the priest, blessing, saith:
\par }\pard\plain \s45\qj\li576\ri576\sb100\sa100\sl360\slmult1\nowidctlpar\adjustright \f1\fs36\cf15 {\b\i Priest:}{ Blessed is the entry of Thy holy ones always, now and ever and unto the ages of ages.
\par Deacon: Amen.}{\fs32 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\qj\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 After that, the deacon goes to the bishop, or to the abbot, and he kisseth the Gospel, if he be present; if not, the priest kisseth it. \line }{\fs32 \~\line }{
\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 When the final verse of the antiphon hath been finished, the deacon goes to the center, and standing in front of the priest, raiseth his hands a little and showing the Holy Gospel, says in a loud voice:}{\fs32  
\par }\pard\plain \qj\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Deacon:}{\fs32  }{\cs47\b\fs36 Wisdom! Aright! 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\qj\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 
Then, having bowed, as also the priest behind him, he goeth into the holy altar; and the deacon immediately layeth the Holy Gospel upon the Holy Table. Then he immediately goeth to his place at the side of the holy table. 
\par And the singers chant:
\par }\pard\plain \li720\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {People: O come, let us worship and fall down before Christ. O Son of God
\par }\pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 If it be a weekday:
\par }\pard\plain \li720\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {Who art wondrous in the saints, save us who chant unto Thee: Alleluia. Once. 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 If it be a Sunday:
\par }\pard\plain \li720\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {Who art risen from the dead, save us who chant unto Thee: Alleluia. 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 on feasts of the Theotokos:}{\fs32 
\par }\pard\plain \li720\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {Through the prayers of the Theotokos, save us who chant unto Thee: Alleluia. 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\qj\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\fs32 \sect }\sectd \linex0\sectdefaultcl \pard\plain \s25\qj\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 
Then the Troparia and Kontakia are chanted according to the Typicon, and when they come to the last Kontakion, the deacon saith to the priest, while bowing his head and holding his orarion with three fingers of his right hand:
\par }\pard\plain \s45\qj\li576\ri576\sb100\sa100\sl360\slmult1\nowidctlpar\adjustright \f1\fs36\cf15 {\b\i Deacon:}{ Bless, master, the time of the thrice-holy.
\par }\pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 And the priest signing him with the sign of the Cross saith: }{\i\fs32\cf15 
\par }\pard\plain \qj\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Priest:}{\fs32  }{\cs47\b\fs36 For holy art thou, O our God, and unto Thee we send up glory to the Father and to the Son and to the Holy Spirit, now and ever ...}{\fs32  }{
\cs44\i\f1\cf6 (and if there be no deacon serving, the priest completes the exclamation) 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\qj\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 And the Kontakion having ended, the deacon cometh out through the holy doo
rs, and standing on the ambo and pointing with his orarion, first to the icon of Christ, saith: 
\par }\pard\plain \qj\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Deacon:}{\fs32  }{\cs47\b\fs36 O Lord, save the pious, and hearken unto us.}{\fs32  
\par }\pard \li720\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {People: O Lord, save the pious and hearken unto us. 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 Then he pointeth to all the people, saying in a loud voice:
\par }\pard\plain \qj\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Deacon:}{\fs32  }{\cs47\b\fs36 And unto the ages of ages. 
\par }\pard \li720\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {People: Amen. {\*\bkmkstart h10}{\*\bkmkend h10}
\par }\pard\plain \s19\sb100\sa100\keepn\nowidctlpar\outlinelevel2\adjustright \b\fs36 {\fs40 The Trisagion
\par }\pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 While the Trisagion is chanted, the priest saith this prayer: 
\par }\pard\plain \qc\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 {\*\bkmkstart h11}{\*\bkmkend h11}The Prayer of the Trisagion Hymn}{\cs44\i\f1\cf6 
\par }\pard\plain \s45\qj\li576\ri576\sb100\sa100\sl360\slmult1\nowidctlpar\adjustright \f1\fs36\cf15 {\b\i Priest:}{ O Holy God, Who restest in the saints, Who art praised with the thrice-holy hym
n by the Seraphim, and art glorified by the Cherubim, and art worshiped by all the heavenly hosts, Who from nonbeing hast brought all things into being, Who hast created man according to Thine image and likeness, and hast adorned him with Thine every gift
;
 Who givest wisdom and understanding to him that asketh, and Who disdainest not him that sinneth, but hast appointed repentance unto salvation; Who hast vouchsafed us, Thy lowly and unworthy servants, to stand even in this hour before the glory of Thy hol
y altar, and to offer the worship and glory due unto Thee: Do Thou Thyself, O Master, accept even from the lips of us sinners the thrice-holy hymn, and visit us in Thy goodness. \line 
Pardon us every sin, voluntary and involuntary; sanctify our souls and bodies,
 and grant us to serve Thee in holiness all the days of our life, through the intercessions of the holy Theotokos, and of all the saints, who from ages past have been pleasing unto Thee. For holy art Thou, O our God, and unto Thee do we send up glory: to 
the Father, and to the Son, and to the Holy Spirit, now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 \sect }\sectd \linex0\sectdefaultcl \pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 
When this is ended, both the priest and deacon themselves say the Trisagion Hymn, making together three bows before the Holy Table. Then the deacon saith to the Priest:}{\fs32  
\par }\pard\plain \s45\qj\li576\ri576\sb100\sa100\sl360\slmult1\nowidctlpar\adjustright \f1\fs36\cf15 {\cs43\b\i\fs28 Deacon:}{ Command, O Master. 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 And they proceed to the high place; and the priest, as he goeth, saith:
\par }\pard\plain \s45\qj\li576\ri576\sb100\sa100\sl360\slmult1\nowidctlpar\adjustright \f1\fs36\cf15 {\cs43\b\i\fs28 Priest:}{\b\i  }{Blessed is he that cometh in the name of the Lord. \line }{\cs43\b\i\fs28 Deacon: }{Bless, Master, the High Throne. 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 And the priest, blessing, sayeth:
\par }\pard\plain \s45\qj\li576\ri576\sb100\sa100\sl360\slmult1\nowidctlpar\adjustright \f1\fs36\cf15 {\cs43\b\i\fs28 Priest:}{\b\i  }{Bless
ed art Thou on the Throne of the glory of Thy Kingdom, Thou that sittest on the Cherubim: always, now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. \line }{\cs43\b\i\fs28 \~Deacon:}{ Amen. 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 It is to be noted that it is not proper for the priest to go up onto the high place, nor to sit ther
eon, but to sit on the South side of the high throne. And upon the conclusion of the Trisagion, the deacon, having come toward the holy doors, saith:
\par }\pard\plain \s19\sb100\sa100\keepn\nowidctlpar\outlinelevel2\adjustright \b\fs36 {\fs40 {\*\bkmkstart h12}{\*\bkmkend h12}The Epistle
\par }\pard\plain \qj\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Deacon:}{\fs32  }{\cs47\b\fs36 Let us attend! 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 And the priest exclaimeth:
\par }\pard\plain \qj\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Priest:}{\fs32  }{\cs47\b\fs36 Peace be unto all.}{\fs32  
\par }\pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 And the reader saith:
\par }\pard\plain \li720\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {Reader: And to thy spirit. 
\par }\pard \qj\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Deacon:}{\fs32  }{\cs47\b\fs36 Wisdom! 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 And the reader, the Prokeimenon, from the Psalms of David. And after the Prokeimenon, the Deacon:}{\fs32 
\par }\pard\plain \qj\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Deacon:}{\fs32  }{\cs47\b\fs36 Wisdom! 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 And the reader, the title of the Epistle}{\cs44\i\f1\cf6 
\par }\pard\plain \li720\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {Reader: The reading is from the Epistle of the Holy Apostle Paul to the Romans or to the Corinthians, or to the Galations 
\par }\pard \qj\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Deacon:}{\fs32  }{\cs47\b\fs36 Let us attend! 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 And when the epistle is concluded, the priest sayeth:
\par }\pard\plain \qj\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Priest:}{\fs32  }{\cs47\b\fs36 Peace be unto Thee that readest. 
\par }\pard \li720\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {Reader: And to thy Spirit. 
\par }\pard \qj\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Deacon:}{\fs32  }{\cs47\b\fs36 Wisdom! 
\par }\pard \li720\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {Reader: Alleluia in the ____Tone. 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\qj\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 
While the Alleluia is being chanted, the deacon, taking the censer and incense, approaches the priest, and taking a blessing from him, censeth the Holy Table round about, and the whole altar, and the priest ( but, some cense during the e
pistle reading ) And the priest saith this prayer:
\par }\pard\plain \s19\sb100\sa100\keepn\nowidctlpar\outlinelevel2\adjustright \b\fs36 {\fs40 {\*\bkmkstart h13}{\*\bkmkend h13}\sect }\sectd \linex0\sectdefaultcl \pard\plain \s19\sb100\sa100\keepn\nowidctlpar\outlinelevel2\adjustright \b\fs36 {\fs40 
The Gospel
\par }\pard\plain \qc\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 {\*\bkmkstart h14}{\*\bkmkend h14}The Prayer before the Gospel}{\cs44\i\f1\cf6 
\par }\pard\plain \s45\qj\li576\ri576\sb100\sa100\sl360\slmult1\nowidctlpar\adjustright \f1\fs36\cf15 {\cs43\b\i\fs28 Priest:}{
 Shine forth within our hearts the incorruptible light of Thy knowledge, O Master, Lover of mankind, and open the eyes of our mind to the understanding of th
e preaching of Thy Gospel; instill in us also the fear of Thy blessed commandments, that, trampling down all lusts of the flesh, we may pursue a spiritual way of life, being mindful of and doing all that is well-pleasing unto Thee. For Thou art the enligh
tenment of our souls and bodies, O Christ God, and unto Thee do we send up glory, together with Thine unoriginate Father, and Thy most holy and good and life-creating Spirit, now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen.
\par }\pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 The deacon having put away the cens
er in the usual place, receiveth the Gospel from the priest, and goeth out through the holy doors, a candle preceeding him, and goeth forth and standeth on the ambo, or on the appointed place. 
\par }\pard\plain \qj\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Deacon:}{\fs32  }{\cs47\b\fs36 Bless, master, the bringer of the good tidings of the Holy, Apostle and Evangelist }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6 N.}{\cs47\b\fs36  
\par }\pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 The priest signing him with the sign of the cross, saith:
\par }\pard\plain \qj\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Priest:}{\fs32  }{\cs47\b\fs36 May God, through the intercessions of the holy, glorious, all praised Apostle and Evangelist }{\cs44\b\i\f1\cf6 N.,}{\cs47\b\fs36 
 give speech with great power unto Thee that bringest good tidings, unto the fulfillment of the Gospel of His Beloved Son, our Lord Jesus Christ. 
\par }{\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Deacon:}{\fs32  }{\cs47\b\fs36 Amen.}{\fs32  
\par }\pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 And the priest standing before the Holy Table (in current practice, behind the Holy Table, at the South side of the high place), and looking toward the wes
t, and blessing the people, exclaimeth: 
\par }\pard\plain \qj\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Priest:}{\fs32  }{\cs47\b\fs36 Wisdom, Aright! Let us hear the Holy Gospel. Peace be unto all}{\fs32 .    }{People: And to thy spirit. 
\par }{\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Deacon:}{\fs32  }{\cs47\b\fs36 The Reading from the Holy Gospel according to Saint }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6 N}{\cs47\b\fs36 .        }{People: Glory to Thee, O Lord, glory to Thee. 
