\par }\pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 The holy doors are opened. \line \~\line The prayer which the priest reciteth secretly, while the Cherubimic hymn is being chanted: 
\par }\pard\plain \qc\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 {\*\bkmkstart h27}{\*\bkmkend h27}Prayer of the Cherubimic Hymn}{\cs44\i\f1\cf6 
\par }\pard\plain \s45\qj\li576\ri576\sb100\sa100\sl360\slmult1\nowidctlpar\adjustright \f1\fs36\cf15 {\cs43\b\i\fs28 Priest:}{ None is worthy a
mong them that are bound with carnal lusts and pleasures, to approach or to draw nigh, or to minister unto Thee, O King of glory, for to serve Thee is a great and fearful thing even unto the heavenly hosts themselves. Yet because of Thine ineffable and im
m
easurable love for mankind, without change or alteration Thou didst become man, and didst become our High Priest, and didst deliver unto us the ministry of this liturgical and bloodless sacrifice, for Thou art the Master of all. Thou alone, O Lord our God
,
 dost rule over those in heaven and those on earth, art borne upon the throne of the Cherubim, art Lord of the Seraphim and King of Israel, Thou alone art holy and restest in the saints. I implore Thee, therefore, Who alone art good and inclined to listen
:
 Look upon me Thy sinful and unprofitable servant, and purge my soul and heart of a wicked conscience, and, by the power of thy Holy Spirit, enable me, who am clothed with the grace of the priesthood, to stand before this Thy Holy Table, and to perform th
e
 sacred Mystery of Thy holy and immaculate Body and precious Blood. For unto Thee do I draw nigh, bowing my neck, and I pray Thee: Turn not Thy countenance away from me, neither cast me out from among Thy children, but vouchsafe that these gifts be offere
d
 unto Thee by me, Thy sinful and unworthy servant: for Thou art He that offereth and is offered, that accepteth and is distributed, O Christ our God, and unto Thee do we send up glory, together with Thine unoriginate Father, and Thy most holy and good and
 life-creating Spirit, now and ever and unto the ages of ages. 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 \sect }\sectd \linex0\sectdefaultcl \pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 
When this prayer is completed the priest and the deacon say also the Cherubimic hymn, thrice, the priest with his hands raised up, and the deacon holding his orarion up high with three fingers
 of his right hand, and each time, at the conclusion thereof, they bow once.
\par }\pard\plain \s45\qj\li576\ri576\sb100\sa100\sl360\slmult1\nowidctlpar\adjustright \f1\fs36\cf15 {\b\i Priest:}{ Let us, who mystically represent the Cherubim and chant the thrice-holy hymn unto the life-creating Trinity, now lay aside all earthly cares: 
\line \~\line }{\b\i Deacon:}{ That we may receive the King of all, Who cometh invisibly upborne in triumph by the ranks of angels. Alleluia, alleluia, alleluia. 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 The deacon, taking the censer and placing incense therein, approacheth the priest, (in current practice, he censeth while the priest is saying
 the secret prayer, or the priest, if he serve alone, censeth immediately after the secret prayer) and taking a blessing from him, censeth round about the whole table, and the whole altar, and the whole altar and the priest, and he sayeth the 50th Psalm a
nd the troparia of compunction, and whatsoever he may wish, together with the priest. \line }{\fs32 \~\line }{\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 
And the priest goeth to the table of oblation, the deacon preceding, and the deacon or priest censeth the holy things, praying secretly: 
\par }{\b\i\fs36\cf15 Deacon:}{\f1\fs36\cf15  O God cleanse me, a sinner. }{\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 Thrice \line }{\fs32 \~\line }{\b\i\fs36\cf15 Deacon:}{\f1\fs36\cf15  Lift up, Master.}{\fs36  
\par }{\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 And the priest taking the aer and layeth it upon the deacon's left shoulder saying:
\par }\pard\plain \s45\qj\li576\ri576\sb100\sa100\sl360\slmult1\nowidctlpar\adjustright \f1\fs36\cf15 {\b\i Priest:}{ Lift up your hands to the holies, and bless the Lord.
\par }\pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 Then taking the holy diskos, he placeth it upon the deacon's head, w
ith all attentiveness and reverence, the deacon also having the censer in one of his fingers. The priest himself, taketh the holy chalice in his hands and they come out by the North door, the candle-bearers going before them, and they make the circuit of 
the temple while praying:
\par }\pard\plain \s19\sb100\sa100\keepn\nowidctlpar\outlinelevel2\adjustright \b\fs36 {\fs40 {\*\bkmkstart h28}{\*\bkmkend h28}The Great Entrance
\par }\pard\plain \qj\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Deacon:}{\fs32  }{\cs47\b\fs36 
The Orthodox episcopate of the Russian Church; our lord the Very Most Reverend N., Metropolitan of Eastern America and New York, the First Hierarch of the Russian Church Abroad; and our lord the Most Reve
rend Bishop N., may the Lord God remember in His kingdom, always, now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 After chanting his petition, the deacon immediately enters the sanctuary through the holy doors and kneels on his right knee only, holding the disko
s on the right corner of the holy table. The priest intoneth the following petitions during the entrance.
\par }\pard\plain \qj\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Priest:}{\fs32  }{\cs47\b\fs36 The much suffering Russian Land and its Orthodox people both in the homeland and in the diaspora; this land, its authorities and the faithful 
that dwell therein, may the Lord God remember in His kingdom, always, now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. 
\par The clergy, the monastics, all that are persecuted and suffer for the Orthodox Faith; the founders, benefactors, and the brotherhood of this hol
y temple ( or holy monastery), and all of you Orthodox Christians, may the Lord God remember in His kingdom, always, now and ever, and unto the ages of ages}{\cs47\b\i\fs36 . 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 \sect }\sectd \linex0\sectdefaultcl \pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 
And the priest passeth through the holy doors. And the people say: 
\par }\pard\plain \li720\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {People: May the Lord God remember thy priesthood in His Kingdom, now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen.}{\fs32  
\par }\pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 As the priest passeth through the holy doors the deacon says to him:
\par }\pard\plain \s45\li576\ri576\sb100\sa100\sl360\slmult1\nowidctlpar\adjustright \f1\fs36\cf15 {\b\i Deacon:}{ May the Lord God remember thy priesthood in His kingdom. \line \~}{\b\i Priest:}{ May the Lord God remember t
hy sacred diaconate in His kingdom, always, now and ever, and unto the ages of ages.
\par }{\cs44\i\fs28\cf6 And the priest then placeth the holy chalice on the Holy Table and taking the holy diskos from the head of the deacon, and placeth it on the Holy Table saying:}{\fs32 
\par }{\b\i Priest: }{The noble Joseph, having taken Thy most pure Body down from the Tree and wrapped it in pure linen and covered It with spices, laid It in a new tomb. \line }{\fs32 \~\line }{
In the grave bodily, but in Hades with Thy soul as God; in Paradise with the thief, and on the throne with 
the Father and the Spirit wast Thou Who fillest all things, O Christ the Inexpressible. How life-giving, how much more beautiful than Paradise and truly more resplendent than any royal palace hath Thy tomb appeared, O Christ, the source of our resurrectio
n. 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 
Then taking the veils from the holy diskos and the holy chalice, he layeth them to one side of the altar (in current practice, each is unfolded, and placed on the right and left side of the holy table, over the red cloth and under the cross on each side
.) And taking the aer from the deacon's shoulder, and having censed it, he covereth the Holy Gifts therewith, saying:
\par }\pard\plain \s45\qj\li576\ri576\sb100\sa100\sl360\slmult1\nowidctlpar\adjustright \f1\fs36\cf15 {\b\i Priest:}{ The noble Joseph, having taken Thy most pure Body down from the Tree and wrapped It in pure linen and covered It with spices, laid
 It in a new tomb. 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 And taking the censer from the hand of the deacon, he censeth the Holy Gifts thrice, saying:
\par }\pard\plain \s45\qj\li576\ri576\sb100\sa100\sl360\slmult1\nowidctlpar\adjustright \f1\fs36\cf15 {\b\i Priest:}{ Do good, O Lord, in Thy good pleasure unto Sion, and let the walls of Jerusalem be builded. Then shalt Thou be pleased with a sacrifice
 of righteousness, with oblation and whole-burnt offerings. Then shall they offer bullocks upon Thine altar.
\par }\pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 The holy doors and curtain are closed.
\par \sect }\sectd \linex0\sectdefaultcl \pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 And having returned the censer, and having lowered his phelonion, and having bowed his head, he saith to the Deacon: 
\par }{\b\i\fs32\cf15 Priest:}{\f1\fs32\cf15  Remember me, brother and concelebrant. 
\par }{\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 And the deacon saith to him: 
\par }\pard\plain \s45\qj\li576\ri576\sb100\sa100\sl360\slmult1\nowidctlpar\adjustright \f1\fs36\cf15 {\b\i Deacon:}{ May the Lord God remember thy priesthood in His Kingdom. 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 Then the deacon, bowing his head, holding his orarion with three fingers of his right hand, says to the Priest:
\par }\pard\plain \s45\qj\li576\ri576\sb100\sa100\sl360\slmult1\nowidctlpar\adjustright \f1\fs36\cf15 {\b\i Deacon:}{ Pray for me, holy Master. 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 And the }{\cs44\b\i\f1\cf6 Priest:}{\fs32  
\par }\pard\plain \s45\qj\li576\ri576\sb100\sa100\sl360\slmult1\nowidctlpar\adjustright \f1\fs36\cf15 {\b\i Priest:}{ The Holy Spirit shall come upon thee, and the power of the Most High shall overshadow thee. 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 And the Deacon: }{\fs32 
\par }\pard\plain \s45\li576\ri576\sb100\sa100\sl360\slmult1\nowidctlpar\adjustright \f1\fs36\cf15 {\b\i Deacon:}{ The same Spirit shall minister with us all the days of our life. \line \~}{\b\i Deacon:}{ Remember me, holy Master. 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 And the Priest: 
\par }\pard\plain \s45\li576\ri576\sb100\sa100\sl360\slmult1\nowidctlpar\adjustright \f1\fs36\cf15 {\b\i Priest:}{ May the Lord God remember thee in his kingdom, always, now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. \line \~}{\b\i Deacon:}{ Amen. 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 And having kissed the right hand of the priest, he goeth out the North door, and standing in the usual place, saith:
