\par }\pard \qj\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Deacon:}{\fs32  }{\cs47\b\fs36 That we may be delivered from all tribulation wrath, and necessity, let us pray to the Lord. 
\par }\pard \li720\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {People: Lord, have mercy. }{\fs32 
\par }\pard \qj\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Deacon:}{\fs32  }{\cs47\b\fs36 Help us, save us, have mercy on us, and keep us, O God, by Thy grace. 
\par }\pard \li720\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {People: Lord, have mercy. }{\fs32 
\par }\pard \qj\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Deacon:}{\fs32  }{\cs47\b\fs36 That the whole day may be perfect, holy, peaceful, and sinless, let us ask of the Lord. 
\par }\pard \li720\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {People: Grant this, O Lord.}{\fs32  
\par }\pard \qj\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Deacon:}{\fs32  }{\cs47\b\fs36 An angel of peace, a faithful guide, a guardian of our souls and bodies, let us ask of the Lord.}{\fs32  
\par }\pard \li720\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {People: Grant this, O Lord.}{\fs32  
\par }\pard \qj\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Deacon:}{\fs32  }{\cs47\b\fs36 Pardon and remission of our sins and offenses, let us ask the Lord. 
\par }\pard \li720\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {People: Grant this, O Lord.}{\fs32  
\par }\pard \qj\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 \sect }\sectd \linex0\sectdefaultcl \pard\plain \qj\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Deacon:}{\fs32  }{\cs47\b\fs36 Things good and profita
ble for our souls and bodies, and peace for the world, let us ask of the Lord. 
\par }\pard \li720\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {People: Grant this, O Lord.}{\fs32  
\par }\pard \qj\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Deacon:}{\fs32  }{\cs47\b\fs36 That we may complete the remaining time of our life in peace and repentance let us ask of the Lord.  
\par }\pard \qj\fi720\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {People: Grant this, O Lord.}{\fs32  
\par }\pard \qj\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Deacon:}{\fs32  }{\cs47\b\fs36 A Christian ending to our life, painless, blameless, peaceful; and a good defense before the dread Judgment Seat of Christ, let us ask. \tab \tab \tab \tab   
}{People: Grant this, O Lord.}{\fs32  
\par }{\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Deacon:}{\fs32  }{\cs47\b\fs36 Calling to remembrance our most holy, most pure, most blessed, glorious Lady 
Theotokos and ever-virgin Mary, with all the Saints, let us commit ourselves and each other, and all our life unto Christ our God.    }{People: To thee, O Lord.}{\fs32  
\par }\pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 The deacon moves to stand before the icon of Christ while priest finisheth the prayer of Proskomedia.
\par }\pard\plain \qc\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 {\*\bkmkstart h30}{\*\bkmkend h30}The Prayer of the Proskomedia}{\cs44\i\f1\cf6 
\par }\pard\plain \s45\qj\li576\ri576\sb100\sa100\sl360\slmult1\nowidctlpar\adjustright \f1\fs36\cf15 {\b\i Priest:}{
 O Lord God Almighty, who alone art holy, Who dost accept a sacrifice of praise from them that call upon Thee with their whole heart: Accept also the supplication of us sinners, and bring it to Thy Holy Altar, and
 enable us to offer unto Thee both gifts and spiritual sacrifices for our sins and for the errors of the people, and vouchsafe us to find grace before Thee, that our sacrifice may be acceptable unto Thee, and that the good Spirit of Thy grace may rest upo
n us, and upon these Gifts set forth, and upon all Thy people.
\par }\pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 Exclamation:
\par }\pard\plain \qj\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Priest:}{\fs32  }{\cs47\b\fs36 
Through the compassions of Thine Only-Begotten Son, with Whom Thou art blessed, together with Thine most holy and good and life-creating Spirit: now and ever, and unto the ages of ages.}{\fs32  \tab \tab \tab \tab \tab \tab }{People: Amen.}{\fs32  
\par }\pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 The priest faces the people blessing them saying:
\par }\pard\plain \qj\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Priest:}{\fs32  }{\cs47\b\fs36 Peace be unto all.}{\fs32   \tab \tab \tab \tab }{People: And to thy spirit.}{\fs32  
\par }\pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 The priest turns and faces east and the deacon saith:}{\fs32 
\par }\pard\plain \qj\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Deacon:}{\fs32  }{\cs47\b\fs36 Let us love one another, that with one mind we may confess:}{\fs32  
\par }\pard \li720\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {People: The Father, and the Son, and the Holy Spirit: the Trinity, one in Essence and indivisible.}{\fs32  
\par }\pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 And the priest boweth thrice, saying secretly:
\par }\pard\plain \s45\qj\li576\ri576\sb100\sa100\sl360\slmult1\nowidctlpar\adjustright \f1\fs36\cf15 {\cs43\b\i\fs28 Priest:}{ I will love thee, O Lord, my strength: the Lord is my foundation and my refuge. }{\cs44\i\fs28\cf6 Thrice.}{
\par }\pard\plain \s25\qj\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 And he kisseth the Holy Things that are covered, thus: first the top of the holy diskos, then the top of the holy chalice, and the edge of the holy table before him.
}{\fs32  }{\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 If there be two priests, or more, then they kiss all the holy things, and one another on the shoulder. The senior celebrant saith 'Christ is in our midst' and he that is kissed replieth 'He is and shall be'\~
Likewise the deacons, if there be two or three, kiss each his own orarion, where the figure of the Cross is, and one another on the shoulder,
 saying that which the priests have said. In like manner the deacon on the ambo boweth, on the place where he standeth, and kisseth his orarion where the figure of the cross is, and, then lifting the orarion the deacon says:
\par }\pard\plain \qj\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Deacon:}{\fs32  }{\cs47\b\fs36 The Doors! The Doors! In Wisdom let us attend. 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 As the deacon exclaimeth, the curtain is opened, but the holy doors remain closed.
\par \sect }\sectd \linex0\sectdefaultcl \pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 
The priest lifteth up the aer, and holdeth it over the Holy Gifts. If there be other priests concelebrating, they likewise lift up the holy aer, an
d hold it over the Holy Gifts, waving it and saying secretly, as do the people also, the Confession of Faith: 
\par }\pard\plain \s19\sb100\sa100\keepn\nowidctlpar\outlinelevel2\adjustright \b\fs36 {\fs40 {\*\bkmkstart h31}{\*\bkmkend h31}The Symbol of Faith}{\b0\f1\fs32\cf15 
\par }\pard\plain \s45\qj\li576\ri576\sb100\sa100\sl360\slmult1\nowidctlpar\adjustright \f1\fs36\cf15 {I believe in one God, the Father Almighty, Maker of heaven and earth, and of all things visible and invisible: And in one Lor
d Jesus Christ, the Son of God, the Only-begotten, Begotten of the Father before all ages, Light of Light, True God of True God, Begotten, not made; of one essence with the Father, by whom all things were made: Who for us men and for our salvation came do
w
n from the heavens, and was incarnate of the Holy Spirit and the Virgin Mary, and became man; And was crucified for us under Pontius Pilate, and suffered and was buried; And rose again on the third day, according to the Scriptures; And ascended into the h
e
avens, and sitteth at the right hand of the Father; And shall come again, with glory, to judge both the living and the dead, Whose kingdom shall have no end. And in the Holy Spirit, the Lord, the Giver of Life, Who proceedeth from the Father, Who with the
 
Father and the Son together is worshiped and glorified, Who spake by the Prophets; In One Holy Catholic and Apostolic Church. I Confess one Baptism for the remission of sins. I look for the Resurrection of the dead, And the life of the age to come, Amen. 

\par }\pard\plain \s19\sb100\sa100\keepn\nowidctlpar\outlinelevel2\adjustright \b\fs36 {\fs40 {\*\bkmkstart h32}{\*\bkmkend h32}\sect }\sectd \linex0\sectdefaultcl \pard\plain \s19\sb100\sa100\keepn\nowidctlpar\outlinelevel2\adjustright \b\fs36 {\fs40 
The Anaphora
\par }\pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 At the end of the confession of faith, the deacon, still standing before the icon of Christ with raised orarion says:
\par }\pard\plain \qj\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Deacon:}{\fs32  }{\cs47\b\fs36 Let us stand well; let us stand with fear; let us attend, that we may offer the Holy Oblation in peace. 
\par }\pard \li720\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {People: A mercy of peace, a sacrifice of praise.}{\fs32  
\par }\pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 The priest turneth to bless the people, and saith: 
\par }\pard\plain \qj\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Priest:}{\fs32  }{\cs47\b\fs36 The grace of our Lord Jesus Christ, and the love of God the Father, and the communion of the Holy Spirit, be with you all. 
\par }\pard \li720\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {People: And with thy spirit.}{\fs32  
\par }\pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 The priest turneth back to face the Holy Table, and lifting up his hands, saith: 
\par Exclamation: }{\fs32 
\par }\pard\plain \qj\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Priest:}{\fs32  }{\cs47\b\fs36 Let us lift up our hearts. 
\par }\pard \li720\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {People: We lift them up unto the Lord.}{\fs32  
\par }\pard \qj\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Priest:}{\fs32  }{\cs47\b\fs36 Let us give thanks unto the Lord. 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 All make a prostration, if it be a weekday, but not it be Great Feast of the Lord or the Theotokos.}{\fs32  
\par }\pard\plain \li720\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {People: It is meet and right to worship the Father, and the Son, and the Holy Spirit: The trinity one in essence and indivisible..}{\fs32  
\par }\pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 The deacon enters the sanctuary through the North door and stands a
t the Northwest corner of the holy table, makes three metanias and kisses the corner of the holy table}{\fs32 . \line \~\line }{\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 The priest prayeth:{\*\bkmkstart h33}{\*\bkmkend h33}
\par The First Prayer of the Anaphora}{\cs44\i\f1\cf6 
\par }\pard\plain \s45\qj\li576\ri576\sb100\sa100\sl360\slmult1\nowidctlpar\adjustright \f1\fs36\cf15 {\cs43\b\i\fs28 Priest:}{ It is meet and right to hymn Thee, to bless Thee, to praise Thee, to give thanks unto Th
ee, to worship Thee in every place of thy dominion, for Thou art God inexpressible, incomprehensible, invisible, unattainable, ever-existing, eternally the same, Thou and Thine Only-begotten Son and Thy Holy Spirit. Thou didst call us from nonbeing into b
e
ing, and when we had fallen away, Thou didst raise us up again, and didst not cease to do all things until Thou hadst brought us up to heaven, and hadst bestowed upon us Thy kingdom which is to come. For all these things we give thanks unto Thee, to Thine
 
Only-begotten Son, and to Thy Holy Spirit, for all things whereof we know, and whereof we know not; for the benefits both manifest and hidden which have come upon us. We give thanks unto Thee also for this service which Thou hast been pleased to accept fr
om our hands, though there stand before Thee thousands of archangels and ten thousands of angels, the cherubim and seraphim, six-winged, many-eyed, borne aloft on their wings.
\par }\pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 And here the deacon taketh the holy star from the holy diskos, maketh the sign of the cross above it, and kissing it, layeth it aside as the priest saith:}{\fs32  

\par }{\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 Exclamation: 
\par }\pard\plain \qj\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Priest:}{\fs32  }{\cs47\b\fs36 Singing the triumphal hymn, shouting, crying aloud, and saying: 
\par }\pard \li720\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {People: Holy, Holy, Holy, Lord of Sabaoth; heaven and earth are full of thy glory; Hosanna in the highest: Blessed is he that cometh in the name of the Lord. Hosanna in the highest. {\*\bkmkstart h34}
{\*\bkmkend h34}
\par }\pard \qc\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 The Second Prayer of the Anaphora}{\cs44\i\f1\cf6 
\par }\pard\plain \s45\qj\li576\ri576\sb100\sa100\sl360\slmult1\nowidctlpar\adjustright \f1\fs36\cf15 {\b\i Priest:}{ With these blessed hosts, O Master, Lover of mankind, we also cry aloud and say: Holy art Thou and most holy, Thou, and Thine
 only-begotten Son, and Thy Holy Spirit: holy art Thou and most holy, and majestic is Thy glory, O Thou Who so loved Thy world that Thou gavest Thine Only-begotten Son, that whosoever believeth in Him should not perish, but have everlasting life; Who when
 
He had come and fulfilled all the dispensation for us, on the night in which He was betrayed, or rather gave Himself up for the life of the world, took bread in His holy and most pure and unblemished hands, and when He had given thanks, and had blessed it
, and hallowed it, and broken it, He gave it to His holy disciples and apostles, saying:
\par }\pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 Exclamation: 
\par }\pard\plain \qj\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Priest:}{\fs32  }{\cs47\b\fs36 Take, eat: this is my Body which is broken for you, for the remission of sins. 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\qj\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 While the above is being said, the deacon pointeth out the holy di
skos to the priest, holding his orarion with three fingers of his right hand. Likewise, when the priest saith 'Drink of it, all of you', he pointeth out the holy chalice.}{\fs32 
\par }\pard\plain \li720\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {People: Amen. 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 The priest secretly:}{\fs32  
\par }\pard\plain \s45\qj\li576\ri576\sb100\sa100\sl360\slmult1\nowidctlpar\adjustright \f1\fs36\cf15 {\cs43\b\i\fs28 Priest:}{ And likewise, the cup after supper, saying: 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 Exclamation: 
\par }\pard\plain \qj\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Priest:}{\fs32  }{\cs47\b\fs36 Drink of it, all of you: this is My Blood of the New Testament, which is shed for you and for many, for the remission of sin.}{\fs32  
\par }\pard \li720\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {People: Amen.}{\fs32  
\par }\pard\plain \s45\qj\li576\ri576\sb100\sa100\sl360\slmult1\nowidctlpar\adjustright \f1\fs36\cf15 {\cs43\b\i\fs28 Priest:}{ Mindful, therefore, of this saving commandment and all those things which came 
to pass for us: the cross, the grave, the resurrection on the third day, the ascension into the heavens, the session at the right hand, the second and glorious coming again:
\par }\pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 Exclamation:}{\fs32 
\par }\pard\plain \qj\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Priest:}{\fs32  }{\cs47\b\fs36 Thine own of Thine own we offer unto Thee, in behalf of all, and for all. 
