 Unto thee we offer our whole life and hope O Master, Lover of mankind, and we ask Thee, and pray Thee, and supplicate Thee, vouchsafe us to p
artake of Thy heavenly and dread Mysteries of this holy and spiritual Table, with a pure conscience, unto remission of sins, unto pardon of offenses, unto communion of thy Holy Spirit, unto inheritance of the kingdom of heaven, unto boldness towards Thee;
 not unto judgment}{\cs47\b\f0 ,}{ nor unto condemnation.
\par }\pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 The deacon standeth before the Icon of Christ. The priest, Exclamation:}{\fs32 
