\par }\pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 All make a prostration, if it be a weekday, but not it be Great Feast of the Lord or the Theotokos. 
\par }\pard\plain \qj\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 All:}{\fs32  Our Father, who art in heavens, hallowed be thy Name; thy kingdom come; thy will be done on earth as it is in heaven. Give us this day our daily 
bread; and forgive us our debts, as we forgive our debtors; and lead us not into temptation, but deliver us from the Evil One. 
\par }{\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Priest:}{\fs32  }{\cs47\b\fs36 For Thine is the kingdom, and the power, and the glory, of the Father, and of the Son, and of the Holy Spirit: now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. 
\par }\pard \li720\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {People: Amen. 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 The priest turneth to bless the people and saith:}{\fs32  
\par }\pard\plain \qj\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Priest:}{\fs32  }{\cs47\b\fs36 Peace be unto all. 
\par }\pard \li720\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {People: And to thy spirit.}{\fs32  
\par }\pard \qj\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Deacon:}{\fs32  }{\cs47\b\fs36 Bow your heads unto the Lord. 
\par }\pard \li720\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {People: To thee, O Lord.}{\fs32  
\par }\pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 \sect }\sectd \linex0\sectdefaultcl \pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 And the priest prayeth: 
\par }\pard\plain \qc\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 {\*\bkmkstart h38}{\*\bkmkend h38}The Prayer at the bowing of the heads}{\cs44\i\f1\cf6 
\par }\pard\plain \s45\qj\li576\ri576\sb100\sa100\sl360\slmult1\nowidctlpar\adjustright \f1\fs36\cf15 {\cs43\b\i\fs28 Priest:}{
 We give thanks unto Thee, O King invisible, who by Thine immeasurable might hast created all things, and in the multitude of Thy mercies hast brought all things from non-being into being; do Thou Thyself, O Master, look 
from heaven upon them that have bowed their heads unto Thee, for thy have not bowed down unto flesh and blood, but unto Thee, the awesome God. Do Thou therefore, O Master, distribute these Things here set forth unto us all for good, according to the need 
of each; sail with them that voyage, travel with them that journey, heal the sick, O Thou Physician of our souls and bodies.
\par }\pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 Exclamation:}{\fs32 
\par }\pard\plain \qj\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Priest:}{\fs32  }{\cs47\b\fs36 Through the grace and compassions and love for mankind of Thine Only-begotten Son, with whom thou art blessed, 
together with thy most holy and good, and life-creating Spirit: now and ever, and unto the ages of ages.}{\fs32  
\par }\pard \li720\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {People: Amen.}{\fs32  
\par }\pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 And the priest prayeth: 
