\par }\pard\plain \qj\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Priest:}{\fs32  }{\cs47\b\fs36 Holy Things are for the Holy. 
\par }\pard \li720\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {People: One is Holy, One is Lord: Jesus Christ, to the glory of God the Father. Amen.}{\fs32  
\par }\pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 And the choir chanteth the communion verse of the day, or 
of the saint. (On Sundays, thy chant: Praise the Lord from the heavens: praise Him in the highest. Alleluia, alleluia, alleluia. ) \line \~\line 
And the deacon goeth into the holy altar, and standing at the right hand of the priest who holdeth the Holy Bread saith: 
\par }\pard\plain \s45\qj\li576\ri576\sb100\sa100\sl360\slmult1\nowidctlpar\adjustright \f1\fs36\cf15 {\cs43\b\i\fs28 Deacon:}{ Break the Holy Bread, Master. 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 And the priest, breaking it into four parts with attentiveness and reverence, saith:
\par }\pard\plain \s45\qj\li576\ri576\sb100\sa100\sl360\slmult1\nowidctlpar\adjustright \f1\fs36\cf15 {\cs43\b\i\fs28 Priest:}{ Broken and distributed is the Lamb of God, broken, yet not divided; ever eaten, though never consumed, but sanctifying them 
that partake thereof.
\par }\pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 The deacon, pointing to the holy chalice with his orarion saith:}{\fs32  
\par }\pard\plain \s45\qj\li576\ri576\sb100\sa100\sl360\slmult1\nowidctlpar\adjustright \f1\fs36\cf15 {\cs43\b\i\fs28 Deacon:}{ Fill the holy chalice, Master. 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 The priest, taking the portion which lieth at the top, that is IC, maketh a cross over the holy chalice therewith, saying: 
\par }\pard\plain \s45\qj\li576\ri576\sb100\sa100\sl360\slmult1\nowidctlpar\adjustright \f1\fs36\cf15 {\cs43\b\i\fs28 Priest:}{ The fullness of the Holy Spirit. 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 and thus he placeth it in the holy chalice.}{\fs32  
\par }\pard\plain \s45\qj\li576\ri576\sb100\sa100\sl360\slmult1\nowidctlpar\adjustright \f1\fs36\cf15 {\cs43\b\i\fs28 Deacon:}{ Amen. 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 And taking the warm water, he saith to the Priest: 
\par }\pard\plain \s45\qj\li576\ri576\sb100\sa100\sl360\slmult1\nowidctlpar\adjustright \f1\fs36\cf15 {\cs43\b\i\fs28 Deacon:}{ Bless the warm water, Master. 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 The priest blesseth it, saying:}{\fs32  
\par }{\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Priest:}{\fs32  Blessed is the fervor of Thy saints, always, now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen. 
\par }{\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 And the deacon poureth cruciformly into the holy chalice whatever is sufficient, saying: 
\par }\pard\plain \s45\qj\li576\ri576\sb100\sa100\sl360\slmult1\nowidctlpar\adjustright \f1\fs36\cf15 {\cs43\b\i\fs28 Deacon:}{ The fervor of faith, full of the Holy Spirit. Amen.
\par }\pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 And having set aside the warm water, he standeth near the high place, facing the holy table with his arms folded crosswise. 
\par Concerning the Breaking of the Holy Lamb. \line \~\line It is necessary for thee to know, O priest, that on breaking the Holy Lamb thou must place the part with the sign of the Cros
s downward on the holy diskos, the incised side upward, as before when it was cut. IC, therefore, is placed at the upper side of the holy diskos, which is toward the east. And XC, at the bottom, which is toward the west; and that which is NI, upon the Nor
th side; and KA, on the South side.
\par }\pard \s25\qj\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 
Taking the portion IC, therefore, place it into the holy chalice. And divide the portion XC among the priests and deacons. Divide the other two portions, namely NI and KA, among the communicants in small particles, as man
y as may be sufficient according to thine own estimation. But of the portion of the most holy Theotokos, or of the nine orders of saints, or any others which are upon the holy diskos, thou shalt in no wise communicate anyone; only of the two portions whic
h remain of the Holy Lamb shalt thou give in Communion. \line \~\line 
Furthermore, be it known unto Thee also concerning this: that when thou dost dilute with the holy hot water the Divine Blood of the Master, then thou shalt pour with discretion so that there be enou
gh for all that desire to partake. So also the wine and water, when thou dost pierce the Holy Lamb, thou art to pour at that time an amount sufficient for all; after this, thou shalt pour no more, but only that which is necessary for the dilution at: Holy
 Things are for the Holy, and thus communicate all therefrom. 
\par }\pard\plain \s19\sb100\sa100\keepn\nowidctlpar\outlinelevel2\adjustright \b\fs36 {\fs40 {\*\bkmkstart h40}{\*\bkmkend h40}The Communion of the Clergy
\par }\pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 And the priest and deacon bow thrice as the priest sayeth: 
\par }\pard\plain \s45\li576\ri576\sb100\sa100\sl360\slmult1\nowidctlpar\adjustright \f1\fs36\cf15 {\cs43\b\i\fs28 Priest:}{ O God, cleanse me a sinner. }{\cs44\i\fs28\cf6 Thrice.}{ \line \~O God, absolve, remit and pardon our voluntary and involunta
ry sins, in word and deed, known and unknown, by day and night, in mind and thought; forgive us all, in thy goodness and love for men. 
\par Deacon, Draw nigh. \line \~}{\cs43\b\i\fs28 Deacon:}{ Behold, I approach unto the immortal King and our God. 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\qj\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 And approaching, the deacon maketh 
a bow, reverently asking forgiveness. The priest, holding the Holy Bread, giveth it to the deacon; and the deacon having kissed the hand of him that giveth, receiveth the Holy Bread saying: 
\par }\pard\plain \s45\qj\li576\ri576\sb100\sa100\sl360\slmult1\nowidctlpar\adjustright \f1\fs36\cf15 {\cs43\b\i\fs28 Deacon:}{ Impart unto me, Master the precious and holy Body of our Lord and God and Savior Jesus Christ. 
\par }{\cs43\b\i\fs28 Priest:}{ To the sacred Deacon }{\cs44\i\cf6 N.}{ is imparted the precious, and holy, and most pure Body of our Lord and God and Savior Jesus Christ, unto the remission of his sins, and life everlasting. 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\qj\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 And, bowing his head, the deacon goeth behind the holy table and prayeth as doth the priest saying 'I believe, O Lord', and the rest. 
\par \sect }\sectd \linex0\sectdefaultcl \pard\plain \s25\qj\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 \sect }\sectd \linex0\sectdefaultcl \pard\plain \s25\qj\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 
Likewise the priest, taking one portion of the Holy Bread, saith: 
\par }\pard\plain \s45\qj\li576\ri576\sb100\sa100\sl360\slmult1\nowidctlpar\adjustright \f1\fs36\cf15 {\cs43\b\i\fs28 Priest:}{ Behold, I approach unto Christ, the immortal King and our God. 
\par }{\cs43\b\i\fs28 Priest:}{ The precious and most holy Body of our Lord and God and Savior Jesus Christ is imparted unto me, the Priest }{\cs44\i\cf6 N.,}{ unto the remission of my sins, and life everlasting. 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 And bowing his head, he prayeth, saying:}{\fs32  
\par }\pard\plain \s45\qj\li576\ri576\sb100\sa100\sl360\slmult1\nowidctlpar\adjustright \f1\fs36\cf15 {\cs43\b\i\fs28 Priest:}{ I believe, O Lord, and I confess that Thou
 art truly the Christ, the Son of the living God, who didst come into the world to save sinners, of whom I am chief. Moreover, I believe that this is truly Thy most pure Body, and that this is truly Thine own precious Blood. Wherefore, I pray Thee: Have m
e
rcy on me and forgive me my transgressions, voluntary and involuntary, whether in word or deed, in knowledge or in ignorance. And vouchsafe me to partake without condemnation of Thy most pure Mysteries unto the remission of sins and life everlasting. Amen
. \line \~\line 
Of thy Mystical Supper, O Son of God, receive me today as a communicant; for I will not speak of the Mystery to Thine enemies, nor will I give Thee a kiss as did Judas, but like the Thief do I confess Thee: Remember me, O Lord in Thy kingdom. \line \~

\par Let not the communion of Thy Holy Mysteries be unto me for judgment or condemnation, O Lord, but for healing of soul and body. 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 \sect }\sectd \linex0\sectdefaultcl \pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 
And thus they partake of that which they hold in their hands with fear and all heedfulness. Then rising, the priest taketh the chalice in both hands with the cloth and partaketh thrice from it saying: 
\par }\pard\plain \s45\qj\li576\ri576\sb100\sa100\sl360\slmult1\nowidctlpar\adjustright \f1\fs36\cf15 {\cs43\b\i\fs28 Priest:}{
 Of the precious and holy Blood of our Lord and God and Savior Jesus Christ do I, the servant of God, the priest N., partake unto the remission of my sins and life everlasting. Amen. 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 And thus, having wiped his lips and the holy chalice with the cloth which he holdeth in his hand, he saith:
\par }\pard\plain \s45\qj\li576\ri576\sb100\sa100\sl360\slmult1\nowidctlpar\adjustright \f1\fs36\cf15 {\cs43\b\i\fs28 Priest:}{ Behold, this hath touched my lips, and taketh away mine iniquities, and purgeth away my sins. 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 Then he calleth the deacon, saying: 
\par }\pard\plain \s45\qj\li576\ri576\sb100\sa100\sl360\slmult1\nowidctlpar\adjustright \f1\fs36\cf15 {\cs43\b\i\fs28 Priest:}{ Deacon, draw nigh. 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 And the deacon approacheth, and boweth down once, saying:
\par Impart unto me, Master, the precious and holy Blood of our Lord and God and Savior Jesus Christ. 
\par And the priest saith:}{\fs32  
\par }\pard\plain \s45\qj\li576\ri576\sb100\sa100\sl360\slmult1\nowidctlpar\adjustright \f1\fs36\cf15 {\cs43\b\i\fs28 Priest:}{ The servant of God, the Deacon N., partaketh 
of the precious and holy Blood of our Lord and God and Savior Jesus Christ unto the remission of his sins and life everlasting. 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 The deacon having partaken, the priest saith:
\par }\pard\plain \s45\qj\li576\ri576\sb100\sa100\sl360\slmult1\nowidctlpar\adjustright \f1\fs36\cf15 {\cs43\b\i\fs28 Priest:}{ Behold, this hath touched thy lips, and taketh away thine iniquities, and purgeth away thy sins.
\par }\pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 
It should be known, that if there be those who wish to partake of the Holy Mysteries, the priest breaketh the two portions of the Holy Lamb that remain, that is, NI and KA, into small pieces, so that there be sufficient for all comm
unicants, and then putteth them in the holy cup. \line }{\fs32 \~\line }{\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 And he covereth the holy chalice with its veil, likewise also on the holy diskos he placeth the star and its veil. 
\par }{\fs32 \~\line }{\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 And he saith the prayer:}{\fs32  
\par }\pard\plain \s45\qj\li576\ri576\sb100\sa100\sl360\slmult1\nowidctlpar\adjustright \f1\fs36\cf15 {\cs43\b\i\fs28 Priest:}{ We give thanks unto Thee, O Master, lover of mankind
, benefactor of our souls, that on this very day Thou hast vouchsafed unto us thy heavenly and immortal Mysteries. Direct our way, establish us all in Thy fear, preserve our life, make steadfast our steps, through the intercession and supplications of the
 glorious Theotokos and Ever-Virgin Mary and of all Thy saints. 
\par }\pard\plain \s19\sb100\sa100\keepn\nowidctlpar\outlinelevel2\adjustright \b\fs36 {\fs40 {\*\bkmkstart h41}{\*\bkmkend h41}\sect }\sectd \linex0\sectdefaultcl \pard\plain \s19\sb100\sa100\keepn\nowidctlpar\outlinelevel2\adjustright \b\fs36 {\fs40 
The Communion of the Faithful
\par }\pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 And then they open the doors of the holy altar. And the deacon, bowing once, receiveth the holy chalice with reverence, and approacheth the doors, and elevating 
the holy chalice, showeth it to the people, saying: 
\par }\pard\plain \qj\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Deacon:}{\fs32  }{\cs47\b\fs36 With fear of God, and with faith and love, draw nigh. 
\par }\pard \li720\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {People: Blessed is he that cometh in the Name of the Lord; God is the Lord and hath appeared unto us. 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\qj\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 The Priest saith the prayer 'I believ
e, O Lord and I confess ...' and the rest (as he said himself before communing) with the people. Then those that desire to partake draw nigh. And they come one by one, and bow down with compunction and fear, having their arms folded on their breasts. Then
 each one receiveth the Divine Mysteries. The priest, as he communicateth each one saith:}{\fs32  
\par }\pard\plain \qj\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Priest:}{\fs32  The servant (handmaid) of God }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6 N.}{\fs32 
 partaketh of the precious and holy Body and Blood of our Lord God and Savior Jesus Christ, unto the remission of sins and unto life everlasting. Behold, this hath touched thy lips, and taketh away thine iniquities, and purgeth away thy sins. 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\qj\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 And the deacon wipeth the communicant's lips with the cloth, and the communicant kisseth the holy cup, and bowing, withdraweth. And in thi
s manner do all partake. Meanwhile the following hymn is repeated until all have communicated:
\par }\pard\plain \li720\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {People: Receive ye the Body of Christ; taste ye the Fountain of Immortality}{\fs32  
\par }\pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 And after the last hast communicated:
\par }\pard\plain \li720\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {People: Alleluia, alleluia, alleluia. 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 After c
ommunion, the priest entereth the holy altar and placeth the Holy Things on the Holy Table. The deacon then holdeth the holy diskos over the holy chalice, while emptying the remaining Holy Bread into the chalice, saying these Resurrection Hymns: 
\par }\pard\plain \s45\li576\ri576\sb100\sa100\sl360\slmult1\nowidctlpar\adjustright \f1\fs36\cf15 {\cs43\b\i\fs28 Deacon:}{ H
aving beheld the Resurrection of Christ, let us worship the holy Lord Jesus, the Only Sinless one. We worship Thy Cross, O Christ, and Thy holy Resurrection we hymn and glorify, for Thou art our God, and we know none other beside Thee; we call upon Thy na
me. O come, all ye faithful, let us worship Christ's holy Resurrection, for, behold, through the Cross joy hath come to all the world. Ever blessing the Lord, we hymn His Resurrection, for having endured crucifixion, He hath destroyed death by death. 
\line Shine, shine, O new Jerusalem, for the glory of the Lord is risen upon thee; dance now, and be glad, O Sion; and do thou exult O pure Theotokos, in the rising of Him Whom thou didst bear. \line 
O Christ, Thou great and most sacred Pascha! O Wisdom, Word and Power of God! Grant us to partake of Thee more fully in the unwaning day of Thy Kingdom. 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 He wipeth the holy diskos with the holy sponge exceedingly well, with attentiveness and reverence, saying these words: 
\par }\pard\plain \s45\qj\li576\ri576\sb100\sa100\sl360\slmult1\nowidctlpar\adjustright \f1\fs36\cf15 {\cs43\b\i\fs28 Deacon:}{ By thy precious Blood, O Lord, wash away the sins of those here commemorated, through the intercessions of Thy saints. 
\par }{\cs44\i\fs28\cf6 \sect }\sectd \linex0\sectdefaultcl \pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 The priest blesseth the people, exclaiming:}{\fs32  
\par }\pard\plain \qj\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Priest:}{\fs32  }{\cs47\b\fs36 Save, O God, thy people and bless thine inheritance. 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 And the priest turneth back to the Holy Table, and censeth it thrice, saying secretly: 
\par }{\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Priest:}{\fs32  }{\cs47\b\fs36 Be thou exalted, O God, above the heavens, and Thy glory above all the earth.}{\fs32  
\par }{\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 And the people chanteth:}{\fs32  
\par }\pard\plain \li720\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {People: We have seen the true light, we have received the heavenly Spirit; we have found the true faith, worshiping the indivisible Trinity: for He hath saved us.}{\fs32  
\par }\pard\plain \s25\qj\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 
The deacon taketh the censer from the priest and holdeth it with his right hand. The Priest taketh the holy diskos, placeth it on the deacon's head, and the deacon receiveth it with reverence; looking out through the door
s, saying nothing, he crosseth the holy table between the holy doors and the back of the priest and goeth to the table of oblation, and placeth it thereon. The priest boweth, and taketh the holy chalice, and turning to the doors, looking toward the people
, he saith secretly:}{\fs32  
\par }\pard\plain \s45\qj\li576\ri576\sb100\sa100\sl360\slmult1\nowidctlpar\adjustright \f1\fs36\cf15 {\cs43\b\i\fs28 Priest:}{ Blessed is our God. 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 And aloud: 
\par }\pard\plain \qj\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Priest:}{\fs32  }{\cs47\b\fs36 Always: now and ever, and unto the ages of ages.}{\fs32  
\par }\pard \qj\li720\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {People: Amen. Let our mouths be filled with thy praise, O Lord, that we may hymn thy glory: for thou hast vouchsafed us to partake of thy holy}{\cs47\b\fs36 ,}{
 divine, immortal and life-giving Mysteries. Keep us in thy holiness, that we may meditate upon thy righteousness all the day long. Alleluia, alleluia, alleluia. 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\qj\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 And he goeth to the holy table of oblation and placeth thereon the Holy Things. And as
 he goeth, the deacon censeth the Holy Things, and then giveth the priest the censer, who censeth the Holy Things thrice. 
\par }\pard \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 And the deacon, having uncrossed his orarion and placed it upon his right shoulder, goeth out by the North door, and standing in the usual place saith: 
\par }\pard\plain \sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\fs32 {\*\bkmkstart h42}{\*\bkmkend h42}
\par }\pard\plain \s19\sb100\sa100\keepn\nowidctlpar\outlinelevel2\adjustright \b\fs36 {\fs40 The Litany of Thanksgiving
\par }\pard\plain \qj\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Deacon:}{\fs32  }{\cs47\b\fs36 
Aright! Having partaken of the divine, holy, most pure, immortal, heavenly, life-creating, fearful Mysteries of Christ, let us duly give thanks unto the Lord. 
\par }\pard \li720\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {People: Lord, have mercy. 
\par }\pard \qj\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Deacon:}{\fs32  }{\cs47\b\fs36 Help us, save us, have mercy on us; and keep us, O God, by Thy grace. 
\par }\pard \li720\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {People: Lord, have mercy. }{\fs32 
\par }\pard \qj\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Deacon:}{\fs32  }{\cs47\b\fs36 Having asked that the whole day may be perfect, holy, peaceful, and sinless, let us commit ourselves and one another, and all our life unto Christ our God. 

\par }\pard \li720\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {People: To thee, O Lord.}{\fs32  
\par }\pard\plain \s25\qj\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 
The deacon standeth before icon of Christ. The priest, having folded the antiminsion, and holding the Gospel upright, maketh over the antiminsion the sign of the cross with the Gospel, and layeth it upon the antiminsion, as he exclaimeth: 
\par }\pard \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 Exclamation:}{\fs32 
\par }\pard\plain \qj\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Priest:}{\fs32  }{\cs47\b\fs36 
For thou art our sanctification, and unto Thee do we send up glory: to the Father and to the Son and to the Holy Spirit, now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. 
\par }\pard \li720\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {People: Amen.}{\fs32  
\par }\pard \qj\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Priest:}{\fs32  }{\cs47\b\fs36 Let us depart in peace. 
\par }\pard \li720\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {People: In the name of the Lord.}{\fs32  
\par }\pard \qj\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Deacon:}{\fs32  }{\cs47\b\fs36 Let us pray to the Lord. 
\par }\pard \li720\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {People: Lord have mercy.}{\fs32  \sect }\sectd \linex0\sectdefaultcl \pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 
The priest goeth out through the holy doors and standeth on the solea or in the midst of the church, facing East. 
\par }\pard\plain \qc\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 {\*\bkmkstart h43}{\*\bkmkend h43}The Prayer before the Ambo}{\cs44\i\f1\cf6 
\par }\pard \qj\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Priest:}{\fs32  }{\cs47\b\fs36 O Lord, who dost bless t
hem that bless Thee and sanctify them that put their trust in Thee: Save Thy people and bless Thine inheritance; preserve the fullness of Thy Church, sanctify them that love the beauty of Thy house; do Thou glorify them by Thy divine power, and forsake us
 
not that hope in Thee. Give peace to Thy world, to Thy churches, to the priests, and to all Thy people. For every good gift and every perfect gift is from above, and cometh down from Thee, the Father of lights, and unto Thee do we send up glory and thanks
giving and worship: to the Father, and to the Son, and to the Holy Spirit, now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. 
\par }\pard \li720\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {People: Amen.}{\fs32  
\par }\pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 Then:}{\cs44\i\f1\cf6  
\par }\pard\plain \li720\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {People: Blessed be the name of the Lord, henceforth and forevermore. }{\cs44\i\f1\fs20\cf6 Thrice}{. 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 And Psalm 33 sung with sweet melody:}{\fs32  
\par }\pard\plain \li720\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {People: I will bless the Lord at all times, His praise shall continually be in my mouth. \line In the Lord shall my soul be praised; let the meek hear and be glad. \line 
O magnify the Lord with me, and let us exalt His name together. \line I sought the Lord, and He heard me, and delivered me from all my tribulations. \line Come unto Him, and be enlightened, and your faces shall not be ashamed. \line 
This poor man cried, and the Lord heard him, and saved him out of all his tribulations. \line The angel of the Lord will encamp round about them that fear Him, and will deliver them. \line 
O taste and see that the Lord is good; blessed is the man that hopeth in Him. \line O fear the Lord, all ye His saints; for there is no want to them that fear Him. \line Rich men have turned poor and gone hungry; but they t
hat seek the Lord shall not be deprived of any good thing. \line Come ye children, hearken unto me; I will teach you the fear of the Lord. \line What man is there that desireth life, who loveth to see good days? \line 
Keep thy tongue from evil, and thy lips from speaking guile. \line Turn away from evil, and do good; seek peace, and pursue it. \line The eyes of the Lord are upon the righteous, and His ears are opened unto their supplication. \line 
The face of the Lord is against them that do evil, utterly to destroy the remembrance of them from the earth. \line The righteous cried, and the Lord heard them, and He delivered them out of all their tribulations. \line 
The Lord is nigh unto them that are of a contrite heart, and He will save the humble of spirit. \line Many are the tribulations of the righteous, and the Lord shall deliver them out of them all. \line 
The Lord keepeth all their bones, not one of them shall be broken. \line The death of sinners is evil, and they that hate the righteous shall do wrong. \line The Lord will redeem the souls of His servants, and none of them will do wrong that hope in Him. 

\par }\pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 
The priest goeth through the holy doors and standeth at the holy table, and the deacon, having entered by the North door, layeth his head upon the holy table, to the left of the priest. And the priest saith the following prayer. 
\par }\pard\plain \qc\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 {\*\bkmkstart h44}{\*\bkmkend h44}The Prayer said when the Holy Things are to be consumed}{\cs44\i\f1\cf6 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\qj\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\b\i\fs32\cf15 Priest:}{\f1\fs32\cf15 
 O Christ our God, who art thyself the fulfillment of the law and the prophets, who didst fulfill all the dispensation of the Father: fill our hearts with joy and gladness always: now and ever, and unto ages of ages. Amen. 
\par }\pard \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 And the priest blesseth the deacon, who then goeth to the holy table of oblation to consume the Holy Things.}{\fs32  \line \~\line }{\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 
If the priest serve alone, he consumeth the Holy Things at this time, and if the need arises, the people, after finishing Psalm 33, repeat the last four verses of the psalm until the priest has finished consuming the Holy Things.}{\fs32  \line \~\line }{
\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 And the priest standeth in the midst of the holy doors and blesseth the people saying: 
\par }\pard\plain \qj\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Priest:}{\fs32  }{\cs47\b\fs36 The blessing of the Lord be upon you, through His grace and love for mankind, always, now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. 
\par }\pard \li720\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {People: Amen. {\*\bkmkstart h45}{\*\bkmkend h45}
\par }\pard\plain \s19\sb100\sa100\keepn\nowidctlpar\outlinelevel2\adjustright \b\fs36 {\fs40 \sect }\sectd \linex0\sectdefaultcl \pard\plain \s19\sb100\sa100\keepn\nowidctlpar\outlinelevel2\adjustright \b\fs36 {\fs40 The Dismissal
\par }\pard\plain \qj\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Priest:}{\fs32  }{\cs47\b\fs36 Glory to thee, O Christ our God and our hope, glory to thee.}{\fs32  
\par }\pard \li720\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {People: Glory to the Father, and to the Son, and
 to the Holy Spirit: both now and ever, and unto ages of ages. Amen. Lord, have mercy; Lord, have mercy; Lord, have mercy. Father (Master, if a bishop is present, whether he serve of not), bless. 
\par }\pard \sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Priest:}{\fs32  }{\cs47\b\fs36 May Christ our true God, }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6 (insert the appointed characteristic phrase, on Sundays, 'Who arose from the dead'}{\cs47\b\i\fs36 ),}{\cs47\b\fs36 
 through the intercessions of his most pure Mother; }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6 (and the rest}{\cs44\b\f1\cf6 )}{\cs47\b\fs36  of our father among the saints, John Chrysostom, Archbishop of Constantinople; }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6 
(and of the saint(s) whose temple it is and whose day it is);}{\cs47\b\fs36  of the holy and Righteous Ancestors of God, Joachim and Anna; and of all the saints: have mercy on us and save us, for He is good and the Lover of mankind.}{\fs32  
\par }\pard \li720\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {People: Amen. The Orthodox episcopate of the Russian Church; our Lord the Very Most Reverend Metropolitan }{\cs44\i\f1\cf6 N.,}{
 First Hierarch of the Russian Church Abroad; and our lord the Most Reverend Bishop }{\cs44\f1\cf6 N.;}{ the brotherhood of this holy temple, and all Orthodox Christians: preserve, O Lord, for many years! 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 At this point, the priest may serve a moleben, if he wish. \line \~\line 
The cross is then venerated by the faithful who have not received the Holy Mysteries, and the antidoron is distributed. Those who have communed venerate the cross after the Thanksgiving prayers.}{\fs32  
\par }\pard\plain \sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\fs32 
